PITCH
Opening (First 10 Seconds)

“Hey, is this [Name]?
Hey, this is Tony — I’m a local web designer. I actually built a quick concept website for Three Dimensional Empire and sent a link over earlier. I just wanted to see if you had a chance to take a look at it.”

(Pause and let them answer.)

If They Haven’t Seen It Yet

“No worries at all. It’s just a quick demo I put together to show how the business could look online — things like showing your work, getting customers to contact you, and making the brand look really professional.

It only takes about 30 seconds to look at. If you're near your phone or computer I can walk you through it really quick.”

If They Did See It

“Awesome. I’m curious what you thought of it.
I built it to give a clean, modern look that helps customers understand what you do right away.”

(Let them talk first.)

Your Value Pitch (Keep it Simple)

“Most businesses lose customers because people search online and don’t see a strong website.

The goal with this was to make Three Dimensional Empire look like the top option immediately when someone lands on the page.”

(Short pause)

“It’s also designed to bring in calls and messages directly from the site.”

The Offer

“So if you liked the direction, I can finish it out with your photos, services, and contact info and have it fully live pretty quickly.”

(Pause)

“Are you currently working with a website already or would this be something you'd want to set up?”

If They Show Interest

“Perfect. What I usually do is finish the site, connect the domain, and make sure everything works on phones and Google.

It ends up being a simple setup and then you own the site.”

(Then transition to pricing.)

If They Say “Not Right Now”

“No problem at all. I’ll leave the demo up for you. If you ever decide you want something like that for the business, just reach out and I can finish it.”

One Small Sales Trick That Works

When you talk about it, say:

“The website I built for you”

Not

“a website I built”

That subtle wording makes them feel ownership of it already.

Bonus Line (Very Effective)

If the conversation slows:

“Honestly I built it because I thought Three Dimensional Empire deserved a website that looked as strong as the work you guys do.”

People respond well to that.